reviews:
These were not a disappointment. I am a runner and bought these for running. I have worn them a few times. Last time, I did a long run (over 20 km). They were comfortable. No chafing at all!! The pockets are very practical. The legs stayed put throughout. However, there are a few things that are not ideal. The elastic on the waist is a bit “funny”. It is thick and seems to pucker when you are not wearing them. Having said this, they are comfortable on. I am a bit worried that the waistband will wear out sooner than my other running shorts, but thus far, it is holding up. The material is thick. On very hot days, these are not the running shorts I would reach for. Despite the little “complaints”, I would recommend these to long distance runners.

Edit: I have since ordered 2 more of these. They are great and I highly recommend them for runners.

reviews: My waist is 28" so I was between size S and M. I sized down to size S for the compression. Fit is perfect for high intensity sports. 100% squat proof, no slipping down, no gaping waistband on the back, and cuffs seams don't dig into the leg. The only problem I have is that the 2 pairs I own (both size S) have different inseams. The black space dye (right) is 6" inseam as advertised, but the grey marbled (left) is 7.25" inseam. Taking a star off for the inconsistency, but otherwise these shorts are amazing for the price.
